# Adaptor Integration Flow – Quick Reference (for Cursor)

## Adapter/ATS Name Mapping
Make the search based on the below and store the ats name list from this search as `ats_name_list`
```shell
grep -r "ADAPTER_REGISTRY" www/ats/ats_utils.py
```

## Inputs Required
Mandatory:
- `group_id: {{group_id}}`
- `ats_name: {{ats_name}}`  <!-- Validate this input against `ats_name_list` -->
- `ats_config`: default is `'ats_config'`
- `system_id: {{system_id}}`

Validation:
- If **any field is missing**, prompt for details and HALT further steps.
- Validate `ats_name` against `ats_name_list` and confirm final interpretation.
- Print final values for:
  - group_id
  - ats_name
  - ats_config
  - system_id

## Extract Config
Run the following to extract the ATS config:
```shell
python Agent/Scripts/config_checker.py --group-id {{group_id}} --config-name ats_config --system-id {{system_id}}
```
- Store result as: `customer_ats_config`
- Note: `ats_name` is not a valid argument for this command

## DAG Context
### Search Logic
A DAG is relevant to an adapter if:
1. It executes `sync-worker.py`, and
2. Either:
   - Has `--adapter {ats_name}`
   - Or has no `--adapter` flag (i.e., global)
- All the dags are mentioned in this file `/www/airflow_v2/dags_config.json`

### DAG Context Storage
Each DAG should be stored as `adaptor_dag` in context with this simplified structure:
```xml
<dags>
  <dag>
    <name>dag_name</name>
    <file_path>scripts/airflow/dags-common/filename.py</file_path>
    <description>Human readable description</description>
    <schedule_interval>cron_expression</schedule_interval>
    <frequency>Human readable frequency</frequency>
    <entity>entity_type</entity> <!--Entity name from the dag or inferred top level entity name from dag name -->
    <adapter>adapter_name_or_global</adapter>
    <command_parameters>
        <parameter name="is_entity_enabled">Yes, Only if entity_type present in customer_ats_config.sync_settings.entities[]</parameter>
        <parameter name="is_sync_enabled">dag (sync) are enabled by default unless customer_ats_config.sync_settings.sync_source_settings.[dag_name].enabled:false </parameter>
      <parameter name="lookback_hours">hours</parameter>
      <parameter name="lookback_hours_override">lookback hours present in customer_ats_config.sync_settings.sync_source_settings.dag_name.lookback_hours</parameter>
      <!-- Only include above parameters -->
    </command_parameters>
  </dag>
  ...
</dags>
```

## Integration Sync-Specific Context

### Enhanced Outbound Sync Analysis
The `get_all_operations()` from `www/ats/base.py` method serves as a contract declaring what operations are theoretically possible, while the actual execution depends on config keys in the adapter implementation.

Operation → Handler mapping (static in write_back.py)
Handler → Adapter method call (dynamic via adapter_class property)
Adapter method → Config checks (via credentials.lookup_jsonpath())
Config-driven execution (if enabled, make actual API calls)

- Map all operations to top level entities
- Infer supported Action from the method/operation name. Ex: add_candidate -> Add Candidate
- Check whether the methods raising not-implemented exception or only placeholder is there. Document only if implemented
- Deep analysis on what config/mapping is required for writeback. For Workday - Writeback config is used for writeback in conjunction with trigger_event_config, For SuccessFactors, no special config but based on trigger_event_config, custom_fields_v2.<entity> is used for enabled entity sync.

Document in `outbound_sync`:
```xml
<entities>
    <entity>
      <entity_name>Name of the top level entity. Ex: Employee, Application, Candidate</entity_name>
      <operation>Name of the operation & Action</operation><!-- applicable for workday adaptor only. Populate this based on Outbound Sync Analysis: Ex: Stage Advance, Add candidate, Move Candidate -->
      <Sections>Sections from the entity enabled for writeback</Sections> <!-- For Adaptors, not entire entity data is supported for Writeback. Only section driven config or custom mapping are supported for writeback and taken as a runtime decisions. Ex: Experience, education, outside_experience, etc  -->
      <data_source_1>Workday API</data_source_1> <!-- Writeback Strategy via API/ File-->
      <integration_method>API</integration_method> <!-- Call it "API" as this is from adaptor. Will classify "File" for file based ingestion. RAAS is not to be classified as a file based ingestion -->
<!-- Only include above parameters -->
    </entity>
    ...
<entities>
```

Also, refer config keys from `customer_ats_config` to determine sync enablement and integration method that controls the outbound sync process in codebase. Document the config keys default value and highlight the customer selection as notes to this section

### Enhanced Inbound Sync Analysis
- Use customer_ats_config.sync_settings.entities list for all enabled entities sync. Use this to analyze how the data flow works tracking API calls.

#### Workday Specific Knowledge
- If Workday Adaptor, check if there is a hybrid data source approach via API. Data sync will make API calls to WD ODATA as well as RAAS Report Service depends on config enablement in custom_raas_list_report_v2. RAAS Report data is considered for supplement data that gets combined with API data.
- **Sync Approach Analysis** The `entities_with_only_raas_list_enabled` config key is the point of control that determines RAAS only entity and `customer_ats_config.custom_raas_list_report_v2.<entity>` (infer top level entity name) config key is the point of control that holds the report config.
  - RAAS-Only: Entity listed → Skip standard API completely
  - API-Only: Entity NOT listed + No RAAS configured → Standard API only <!--  `custom_raas_list_report_v2` will have entity report config -->
  - Hybrid: Entity NOT listed + RAAS configured → Use both approaches

#### inbound_sync Context Storage
Store the Inbound Integration approach as `inbound_sync` in the below format for each entity
```xml
<entities>
    <entity>
      <entity_name>Name of the top level entity. Ex: Employee</entity_name>
      <dual_source>Yes/ No</dual_source> <!-- applicable for workday adaptor only. Populate this based on Sync Approach Analysis -->
      <data_source_1>Workday API</data_source_1> <!-- If dual source, API is source 1. If single source then classify it as source 1 -->
      <data_source_2>Workday RAAS</data_source_2> <!-- RAAS, only when its dual source -->
      <integration_method>API</integration_method> <!-- Call it "API" as this is from adaptor. Will classify "File" for file based ingestion. RAAS is not to be classified as a file based ingestion -->
<!-- Only include above parameters -->
    </entity>
    ...
<entities>
```

